Program: The Forum
Title: The Forum in Beijing
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01kdgtr
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 4 Nov 2013
Bridget Kendall chairs a wide-ranging discussion in Beijing about the internet in China: does the rise of digital communication empower the Chinese individual or the state? How is the social media explosion changing the nature of Chinese society? How much is free expression really curtailed by the Great Firewall of China and the recent legislation aimed at curbing the spread of 'rumours' on the net? And is the ability to share the minutiae of their lives online making the young in China politically apathetic? Photo credit: Jackie Zhang Show less